<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d188</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">188</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-05-18T02:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-05-18T02:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-18T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-18T02:00:00-05:00" n="188" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d188">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-18T16:00:00+09:00">May 18, 1948—4 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 18—9:41 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>892. Personal for Butterworth. Heartily approve suggested statement by Secretary
                    on occasion inauguration President and Vice President May 20, Deptel 735 [<hi rend="italic">734</hi>], May 14, 7 p. m.<note n="48" xml:id="d188fn48">The
                        statement was released to the press on May 20; see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, May 30, 1948, p. 713.</note> Such statement
                    will greatly strengthen my hands in discussion I plan to have with Gimo as soon
                    as possible, following inauguration, in which I hope to stress my belief that
                    reform movement is irresistible and that unless he goes along with it, he will
                    inevitably fail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
